## Sitemap Update Checklist

When adding new content:

- [ ] Add new URL to `sitemap.xml`
- [ ] Set appropriate priority:
  - Homepage: 1.0
  - Main articles: 0.9
  - Secondary articles: 0.8
- [ ] Set changefreq:
  - Homepage: "weekly"
  - Articles: "monthly"
- [ ] Update lastmod date to current date (YYYY-MM-DD format)

## README Update Triggers

Update README.md when:
- [ ] Adding new article → Update published articles section
- [ ] Adding new project → Update project listings
- [ ] Major feature addition → Update feature list
- [ ] Changing site structure → Update navigation info

## Article SEO Best Practices

### Title Structure
- Use emoji prefix for visual consistency
- Keep under 60 characters for optimal display
- Include relevant keywords naturally

### Description Guidelines
- 150-160 characters for optimal snippet display
- Include primary keywords naturally
- Make it compelling and descriptive
- Avoid keyword stuffing

### Content Structure
- Use proper heading hierarchy (H1, H2, H3)
- Include internal links to related articles
- Add alt text to all images
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Favicon Requirements

Every new HTML page must include:
```html
<!-- Favicon -->
<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="../favicon.svg">
<link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="../favicon.ico">
<link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="../favicon.svg">
```

## Structured Data Requirements

### For Articles
- [ ] Article schema (JSON-LD) with headline, description, image, author, dates
- [ ] BreadcrumbList schema (JSON-LD) for navigation hierarchy
- [ ] Article date meta tags (article:published_time, article:modified_time, article:author)

### For Homepage
- [ ] Person schema (JSON-LD) with name, jobTitle, url, sameAs (social profiles), description

## Quality Checklist

Before publishing new content:

- [ ] All meta tags present and accurate
- [ ] Article date meta tags included (published_time, modified_time, author)
- [ ] Structured data (JSON-LD) added (Article + BreadcrumbList for articles, Person for homepage)
- [ ] OG image uses assets/og/[filename]-og.png format (not assets/profile.jpg)
- [ ] Twitter Card image included
- [ ] Sitemap updated
- [ ] Images have descriptive alt text
- [ ] Internal links added where relevant
- [ ] Favicon links included
- [ ] Mobile responsive design verified
- [ ] No broken links
- [ ] Consistent styling with existing content
